description.text:
Print with a bunch of bottom layers, a perimeter or two, and don't forget to turn off the infill and top layers. You don't want top layers, no ma'am.  
You <em >do</em> want to drill a couple of holes in the bottom for the goblins to get out or something.  
I had to print the tray at 95% to make it fit on my Printrbot Plus. There is still plenty of room for the pot, though, so I say &quot;good.&quot;
